WEBVTT

00:00.133 --> 00:01.935
Previously on
"Splitting Up Together"...

00:01.935 --> 00:03.403
It's not a first date.
Of course not.
Why would it be?

00:03.403 --> 00:04.571
I'm sorry. Is this
making you feel weird?

00:04.571 --> 00:08.141
It's not weird at all.
Not at all.

00:08.141 --> 00:09.943
Vlad: You're still in love
with your ex-husband.

00:09.943 --> 00:10.944
I am not!

00:10.944 --> 00:12.980
To me, you feel
off the market.

00:12.980 --> 00:15.816
Well, I'm not off the market.
I am on the market.

00:15.816 --> 00:17.117
What are we?

00:17.117 --> 00:18.018
Nothing.

00:18.018 --> 00:19.486
People are buying that?

00:19.486 --> 00:21.054
[ Chuckles ]

00:21.054 --> 00:22.155
Beg pardon?

00:22.155 --> 00:23.690
This has everything
to do with you

00:23.690 --> 00:26.860
and your unresolved feelings
for Martin.

00:28.996 --> 00:31.298
Martin: Hey, Lena.

00:31.298 --> 00:32.799
Martin.
What's wrong?

00:32.799 --> 00:35.369
You cheating on me?
With that Russian contractor?

00:35.369 --> 00:37.638
What? We're not even
together anymore.

00:37.638 --> 00:39.239
You're dating
another woman.

00:39.239 --> 00:40.641
♪♪

00:40.641 --> 00:42.676
There is no other woman.

00:42.676 --> 00:44.544
There never will be
another woman.

00:44.544 --> 00:45.879
You know that.

00:45.879 --> 00:48.782
[ Thompson Twins'
"If You Were Here" plays ]

00:48.782 --> 00:51.218
♪ If you were here ♪

00:51.218 --> 00:54.321
♪ I could deceive you ♪

00:54.321 --> 00:57.391
♪♪

00:57.391 --> 00:58.759
It's a bodysuit.

01:00.260 --> 01:02.362
It has snaps.

01:02.362 --> 01:03.897
Oh.

01:03.897 --> 01:05.799
[ Snaps pop ]

01:05.799 --> 01:07.200
[ Loud pop ]
[ Gasps ]

01:07.200 --> 01:08.535
[ Panting ]

01:08.535 --> 01:10.003
[ Birds chirping ]

01:10.003 --> 01:11.071
[ Chuckles ]

01:11.071 --> 01:12.673
♪♪

01:12.673 --> 01:15.943
♪ Keep giving me hope
for a better day ♪

01:15.943 --> 01:19.646
♪ Keep giving me love
to find a way ♪

01:19.646 --> 01:22.482
♪ Through this heaviness
I feel ♪

01:22.482 --> 01:28.922
♪ I just need someone to say
everything's okay ♪

01:28.922 --> 01:30.590
♪ Everything's okay ♪

01:30.590 --> 01:32.392
-- Captions by VITAC --

01:32.392 --> 01:35.362
Mom, where are our lunches?
It's turkey-and-tahini Tuesday.

01:35.362 --> 01:37.931
Sorry, guys. I must've
slept through my alarm.

01:37.931 --> 01:40.000
Just like that,
Hell hath frozen over.

01:40.000 --> 01:42.269
Okay, Mom's thrown in
the towel.

01:42.269 --> 01:44.838
We're gonna have to
fend for ourselves now.

01:44.838 --> 01:46.707
I'm willing
to be our ruler.

01:46.707 --> 01:49.142
I'd sooner move into the garage
with Dad.

01:49.142 --> 01:50.410
I'm your dad now.

01:50.410 --> 01:51.611
Mason: You'd be
a terrible dad.

01:51.611 --> 01:53.513
[ "If You Were Here" plays ]

01:53.513 --> 01:55.482
[ Indistinct arguing ]
[ Gasps ]

01:55.482 --> 01:57.084
[ Music stops ]
Guys, quiet!

01:57.084 --> 01:58.385
Here.

01:58.385 --> 02:00.087
You're buying lunch today.

02:00.087 --> 02:01.922
Get your stuff.
Come on. Grandpa's outside.

02:01.922 --> 02:04.791
You know he only waits five
minutes before he drives off.

02:07.561 --> 02:11.698
[ Music resumes ]

02:11.698 --> 02:13.734
♪ The rainwater drips ♪

02:13.734 --> 02:18.205
♪ Through a crack
in the ceiling ♪

02:18.205 --> 02:19.473
[ Gasps ]

02:19.473 --> 02:21.408
Ohh!
[ Thud ]

02:21.408 --> 02:22.509
Oh, my God!
[ Groans ]

02:22.509 --> 02:24.478
Oh! Hey.

02:24.478 --> 02:25.879
[ Telephone beeps ]
[ Chuckles ]

02:25.879 --> 02:28.081
Oh, man, are you okay?

02:28.081 --> 02:29.349
Fine. I'm fine.

02:29.349 --> 02:31.284
I'm just -- I'm on hold
for an important business call,

02:31.284 --> 02:32.853
so can I
get back to you?
Mm-hmm.

02:32.853 --> 02:34.321
Maybe I can
get back to you.
Yeah.

02:34.321 --> 02:36.023
Oh, uh,
hey, don't forget,

02:36.023 --> 02:38.225
we need to get a sitter for
parent/teacher night tomorrow.

02:38.225 --> 02:39.259
Don't you forget.

02:40.293 --> 02:42.996
You want me to call
the sitter? I will.

02:42.996 --> 02:45.465
Martin, get out of here.
It is not your week!

02:45.465 --> 02:46.533
Okay.

02:46.533 --> 02:48.135
[ Sighs ]

02:48.135 --> 02:50.437
♪♪

02:50.437 --> 02:53.106
Gene.
What the heck?!

02:53.106 --> 02:53.974
Small world.

02:53.974 --> 02:57.544
Small one block away
from my job.

02:57.544 --> 02:59.279
I don't have
any bread for you, okay?

02:59.279 --> 03:01.181
Okay. [ Chuckles ]

03:01.181 --> 03:02.783
So, is this
your normal look?

03:02.783 --> 03:04.184
You're --
You're a corduroy man?

03:04.184 --> 03:06.720
Mm, yeah. Mama likey.
[ Chuckles ]

03:06.720 --> 03:07.954
This is me. Bye.

03:07.954 --> 03:10.190
Oh. Wait. Um...
[ Clears throat ]

03:10.190 --> 03:12.726
We've been seeing each other
for a couple of weeks now.

03:12.726 --> 03:15.062
I mean, you're
a repeat customer, yeah.

03:15.062 --> 03:18.765
I was kind of feeling like
maybe we were more than that.

03:19.966 --> 03:22.269
I literally
don't even know your name.

03:22.269 --> 03:24.271
[ Laughing ] Oh!

03:24.271 --> 03:25.806
You're gonna love it.

03:26.973 --> 03:28.208
It's Maya.

03:28.208 --> 03:29.276
I'm Maya.

03:30.210 --> 03:32.646
Well, Maya, guess I'll see you
at your next meal,

03:32.646 --> 03:34.314
if you're seated
in my section.
[ Car alarm chirps ]

03:34.314 --> 03:36.083
Oh, come on, Gene.
I don't know what's going on.

03:36.083 --> 03:38.018
Are we --
Are we friends?

03:38.018 --> 03:39.820
Are we enemies?
Are we frenemies?

03:39.820 --> 03:41.922
Are we frennies with bennies?
Are we cuz-bros?

03:41.922 --> 03:43.023
I don't know.
I don't know.

03:43.023 --> 03:44.324
I just really want
to find out.

03:44.324 --> 03:46.960
Preferably before
I give birth, so...

03:46.960 --> 03:49.162
maybe we could
go out on a date.

03:50.230 --> 03:53.200
Fine. But we're going
to Rainforest Buffet.

03:54.568 --> 03:55.902
Okay.

03:55.902 --> 03:57.237
I recently slipped
on some of their tilapia,

03:57.237 --> 03:59.606
so they gave me a voucher
for two free apps.

03:59.606 --> 04:01.575
[ Engine starts ]
Oh. I love tilapia.

04:02.909 --> 04:03.743
Oh --

04:03.743 --> 04:06.780
♪♪

04:06.780 --> 04:09.015
I think he likes us.

04:09.015 --> 04:12.319
♪♪

04:12.319 --> 04:14.254
-Thanks, Lori.
-Sure.

04:14.254 --> 04:15.322
Anxious?

04:16.957 --> 04:18.291
Is it that obvious?

04:18.291 --> 04:20.594
Well, now, I used to have
the worst anxiety

04:20.594 --> 04:21.995
about going to the dentist.

04:21.995 --> 04:23.630
My husband
would have to come in

04:23.630 --> 04:25.999
and hold my hand
the whole time.

04:25.999 --> 04:27.334
[ Chuckles ]

04:27.334 --> 04:28.869
But since he's gone,

04:28.869 --> 04:31.071
I just take one of these.

04:31.071 --> 04:31.738
You want?

04:31.738 --> 04:33.140
Oh! No, thank you.

04:33.140 --> 04:35.842
I don't do drugs.
I'm not a druggie.

04:35.842 --> 04:38.478
Are you sure?
Because these are herbal.

04:38.478 --> 04:41.014
[ Drill whirring ]

04:41.014 --> 04:42.516
Okay, yeah.
I will take one. Thanks.

04:42.516 --> 04:43.850
Oh, good.

04:43.850 --> 04:46.086
[ Whirring continues ]

04:46.086 --> 04:46.953
Oh.

04:46.953 --> 04:48.622
Just for later.
[ Chuckles ]

04:48.622 --> 04:50.090
[ Chuckles ]

04:50.090 --> 04:50.991
[ Button snaps ]

04:50.991 --> 04:52.926
[ Whirring continues ]

04:52.926 --> 04:55.428
So, is your husband
not with us any longer?

04:55.428 --> 04:57.164
He's not, no.

04:57.164 --> 05:00.033
He's with that jezebel,
Eleanor.

05:00.033 --> 05:03.870
And she's the reason
for the rising chlamydia rates

05:03.870 --> 05:05.906
among the elderly.

05:05.906 --> 05:08.675
She's just got a messy
little crinkum-crankum,

05:08.675 --> 05:09.976
if you know what I mean.

05:10.744 --> 05:12.579
I think I do.
Mm.
[ Door opens ]

05:12.579 --> 05:15.749
[ Whirring continues ]
Lena, we're ready for you.

05:17.017 --> 05:18.785
How did you say
this happened?

05:18.785 --> 05:20.120
Well...

05:20.120 --> 05:24.291
I had this erotic dream
about my ex-husband,

05:24.291 --> 05:27.260
wherein he reached down
and unsnapped my bodysuit.

05:27.260 --> 05:28.328
Ohh!

05:28.328 --> 05:30.063
And then when I woke up,
I ran face-first

05:30.063 --> 05:33.166
into the fridge door
just to avoid seeing him.

05:33.166 --> 05:34.935
[ Chuckles ]

05:34.935 --> 05:36.536
The whole thing's
kind of hilarious,

05:36.536 --> 05:38.171
if you think about it.

05:38.171 --> 05:40.874
I bet he would think
it's hilarious, too.

05:42.275 --> 05:44.845
"To: Martin.

05:44.845 --> 05:47.414
Subject: Hilarious."

05:47.414 --> 05:49.015
Are you feeling okay?

05:49.015 --> 05:50.116
Who, me?
Mm-hmm.

05:50.116 --> 05:51.985
I'm legit.
Oh, okay.

05:53.887 --> 05:57.157
Aw, man!
No signal?

05:57.157 --> 05:59.693
Message will be saved
in my outbox?

05:59.693 --> 06:01.194
Well, bad news.

06:01.194 --> 06:03.797
That tooth of yours is cracked
all the way up to the root,

06:03.797 --> 06:06.833
so we're gonna have to do
an emergency root canal.

06:06.833 --> 06:08.835
[ Inhales sharply ]
Yeah.
Yeah.

06:08.835 --> 06:12.138
The thing is,
I don't do so well...

06:14.507 --> 06:15.976
I don't do so well.

06:15.976 --> 06:17.544
Yeah. We know.

06:17.544 --> 06:19.145
Everyone knows.

06:20.046 --> 06:22.349
Might I suggest
some sedation?

06:22.349 --> 06:25.252
Yeah. You can suggest it.
You can do it.

06:25.252 --> 06:26.653
Uh...

06:26.653 --> 06:28.321
Take me to the moon!

06:29.689 --> 06:31.458
[ Gas hissing ]

06:31.458 --> 06:32.959
Mm. Oh!

06:32.959 --> 06:34.728
Just breathe normally.

06:34.728 --> 06:36.296
Okay.

06:36.296 --> 06:37.998
Oh! Excuse me.

06:37.998 --> 06:40.300
I failed
to disclose something.

06:40.300 --> 06:41.968
I was fed a pill

06:41.968 --> 06:45.338
by a, um,
a kind, old lady.

06:45.338 --> 06:48.141
What if there's some kind
of interaction?

06:48.141 --> 06:51.077
Or, like,
combined drug toxicity?

06:51.077 --> 06:53.780
I'm gonna have the doctor
come and talk to you.

06:53.780 --> 06:56.082
Just try to relax.
[ Gasps ]

06:56.082 --> 06:57.651
Think about that bodysuit.

06:57.651 --> 06:58.685
Okay.

06:58.685 --> 07:02.789
♪♪

07:02.789 --> 07:04.758
I like your voice.

07:04.758 --> 07:06.459
[ Echoing ]
I like your voice.

07:06.459 --> 07:09.329
Nurse: [ Echoing ]
Think about that bodysuit.

07:09.329 --> 07:10.597
[ Giggles ]

07:10.597 --> 07:12.499
Lena: [ Echoing ]
Bodysuit. Bodysuit. Bodysuit.

07:12.499 --> 07:14.634
Miriam: [ Echoing ]
Crinkum-crankum.

07:14.634 --> 07:17.771
[ Panting ]

07:17.771 --> 07:20.173
[ Frantic music plays ]

07:20.173 --> 07:22.509
[ Serene music plays ]

07:22.509 --> 07:24.577
[ Frantic music plays ]
[ Panting ]

07:24.577 --> 07:26.780
[ Serene music plays ]

07:26.780 --> 07:27.981
Ma'am?

07:31.718 --> 07:33.386
[ Knock on door ]

07:33.386 --> 07:34.788
I know.

07:34.788 --> 07:36.323
I know -- she's mad.

07:36.323 --> 07:38.725
She's very mad,
but she can't be that mad,

07:38.725 --> 07:40.093
because she came, right?

07:40.093 --> 07:41.394
You said lunch.

07:41.394 --> 07:42.195
I did.

07:42.195 --> 07:44.564
I have lunch.
Come in.

07:45.665 --> 07:46.633
[ Door closes ]

07:46.633 --> 07:48.668
All right, see?
Look.

07:48.668 --> 07:49.803
Look what I did.

07:49.803 --> 07:52.639
I did this -- all me.

07:52.639 --> 07:54.174
So, what the hell,
dude?

07:54.174 --> 07:55.909
What's up
with the head games?

07:55.909 --> 07:57.510
You begged to stay over
at my place,

07:57.510 --> 07:59.212
and when I finally
say yes, you, like,

07:59.212 --> 08:00.880
make up some stupid lie
and run off.

08:00.880 --> 08:02.682
I know. I just got
a little freaked out.

08:02.682 --> 08:04.050
By what?

08:04.050 --> 08:05.485
I mean, everything's normal
at my house.

08:06.519 --> 08:08.588
Are you just one of those guys
who loves the chase,

08:08.588 --> 08:10.623
and then the second a woman's
interested, you're done?

08:10.623 --> 08:12.659
Are you just one of those women
who likes men

08:12.659 --> 08:14.027
when they seem
uninterested?

08:14.027 --> 08:16.563
[ Cellphone rings ]
Because if so...

08:16.563 --> 08:18.331
I am taking this call.

08:19.566 --> 08:20.567
Hello?

08:22.268 --> 08:23.436
She what?

08:24.437 --> 08:25.438
[ Sighs ]
What?

08:25.438 --> 08:27.574
Well, why didn't
anyone stop her?

08:27.574 --> 08:28.708
Ah, geez.

08:28.708 --> 08:29.676
Okay, no.

08:29.676 --> 08:32.412
Yeah.
I'll be right there.

08:32.412 --> 08:35.115
Okay, full disclosure here --
no phony excuses.

08:35.115 --> 08:37.851
This is me
letting you in.

08:38.818 --> 08:39.919
My wife is missing.

08:39.919 --> 08:40.854
What?

08:40.854 --> 08:42.422
Mm-hmm.
Wow.

08:42.422 --> 08:44.391
I know -- it sounds like a lie,
but I swear it's true.

08:44.391 --> 08:46.059
You just called her
your wife.

08:46.826 --> 08:48.595
Ohh.

08:48.595 --> 08:50.363
Oh, no, that's just because
that's what they called her --

08:50.363 --> 08:52.766
the doctor's office
just now on the phone.

08:52.766 --> 08:54.367
And why would they
do that?

08:54.367 --> 08:56.369
[ Stammers ]

08:56.369 --> 08:57.537
Sexism?

08:57.537 --> 09:01.474
God! It just pisses me off,
you know?

09:01.474 --> 09:04.878
I mean, just the stuff that
you guys have to go through.

09:04.878 --> 09:06.179
[ Exhales sharply ]

09:06.179 --> 09:08.047
Also, I'm still
her emergency contact,

09:08.047 --> 09:09.716
and she's still
on my insurance.

09:09.716 --> 09:11.051
Okay.
Nice meeting you.

09:11.051 --> 09:12.352
No, look, Paige --
Okay.

09:12.352 --> 09:14.487
Clearly, our divorces
are not compatible,

09:14.487 --> 09:16.723
but that doesn't mean
that we can't be.

09:16.723 --> 09:17.991
Look.

09:17.991 --> 09:19.692
Let me go find
my ex-wife

09:19.692 --> 09:21.995
and then take my future one
out for drinks.

09:22.829 --> 09:24.364
Did you just propose
to me?

09:24.364 --> 09:27.467
N-No, I-I-I-I certainly
didn't mean to.

09:27.467 --> 09:31.404
I mean, I literally was
just trying to sound...clever.

09:32.439 --> 09:35.708
And if I'm being honest,
I probably won't marry again.

09:35.708 --> 09:37.577
Although I am open
to living with someone.

09:38.478 --> 09:40.480
Obviously,
Lena would need a room.

09:40.480 --> 09:41.848
[ Laughs ]

09:41.848 --> 09:43.783
Kidding.

09:43.783 --> 09:45.985
So, drinks later?

09:45.985 --> 09:47.620
Hm?

09:47.620 --> 09:48.755
[ Groans ]

09:48.755 --> 09:51.191
I have her belongings.
I just don't have her.

09:51.191 --> 09:53.026
I'm gassing up
Gene's Yaris.

09:53.026 --> 09:55.161
Otherwise, I'd love
to help you look.

09:55.161 --> 09:57.497
Hey. Do you want me
to check the oil?

09:57.497 --> 09:58.298
Who's Gene?

09:58.298 --> 09:59.399
Hey, watch the pump!

09:59.399 --> 10:01.367
Don't let it
get over 6 bucks.

10:01.367 --> 10:02.769
Anything over 6,
you're covering.

10:02.769 --> 10:03.803
Sounds like a winner.

10:03.803 --> 10:05.438
Come on, Maya.
Think.

10:05.438 --> 10:06.873
I don't have time for this
right now.

10:06.873 --> 10:09.843
I just ran out on my date
with Paige after apologizing

10:09.843 --> 10:12.011
for running out
on my previous date with Paige.

10:12.011 --> 10:13.346
[ Cellphone rings ]

10:13.346 --> 10:15.114
Hold on.

10:15.114 --> 10:16.416
I got to take this.

10:16.416 --> 10:18.618
Okay! Bye!

10:18.618 --> 10:19.786
Could you get a towel?

10:19.786 --> 10:20.920
[ Cellphone rings ]

10:20.920 --> 10:22.489
What's up?
Hey, bro.

10:22.489 --> 10:24.390
I just caught Lena's set
at the farmers market.

10:24.390 --> 10:25.692
She's pretty talented.

10:25.692 --> 10:26.593
What?!

10:26.593 --> 10:29.896
[ Reggae music plays ]

10:29.896 --> 10:32.265
♪ Buffalo Soldier ♪

10:33.867 --> 10:35.902
♪ Dreadlock Rasta ♪

10:35.902 --> 10:37.203
Oh, no.

10:37.203 --> 10:39.672
♪ There was
a Buffalo Soldier! ♪

10:39.672 --> 10:43.276
I beg you --
I beg you to stop before --
♪ In the heart of America! ♪

10:43.276 --> 10:45.111
Don't say it.
Don't say it!

10:45.111 --> 10:46.980
♪ Stolen from Africa -- ♪

10:46.980 --> 10:48.414
[ Thud ]
[ Crowd gasps ]

10:48.414 --> 10:50.483
[ Laughing ]
Okay, come on.

10:50.483 --> 10:51.584
Okay.

10:51.584 --> 10:53.586
Hi.

10:53.586 --> 10:54.554
Hi.

10:54.554 --> 10:56.222
Hey!
Yeah, hi!

10:56.222 --> 10:57.690
Hey, sorry.
I'm so sorry.

10:57.690 --> 10:58.791
I'm so sorry.

10:58.791 --> 11:02.095
[ Chanting ] Let her sing!
Legalize it!

11:02.095 --> 11:03.196
It's legal, dude.

11:03.196 --> 11:04.864
What are you doing here?

11:04.864 --> 11:06.166
Gettin' my bone broth on.

11:06.166 --> 11:07.534
That's not a beverage, man.

11:07.534 --> 11:08.902
Hey, you going to
parent/teacher night?

11:08.902 --> 11:10.103
Bye!

11:10.103 --> 11:11.671
Little darling
gonna stir it up?

11:11.671 --> 11:14.574
Lena: [ Jamaican accent ]
Hey, mon! Why ya harsh my vibe?

11:14.574 --> 11:16.376
Um, okay, look,
I'm gonna drop you off

11:16.376 --> 11:18.444
so you can sleep off
that offensive accent.

11:18.444 --> 11:20.313
I will go
to parent/teacher night.

11:20.313 --> 11:23.082
Are you kidding me?
I'm not missing parent/teacher.

11:23.082 --> 11:25.585
I am a parent, Martin.

11:25.585 --> 11:27.820
Education is
my top priority.

11:27.820 --> 11:29.188
Lena, but you're --

11:29.188 --> 11:31.457
[ Goofily ] My candidacy
was founded on education.

11:31.457 --> 11:33.293
[ Laughing ]
Oh, my gosh.

11:33.293 --> 11:34.994
Okay. Whatever.

11:34.994 --> 11:37.430
If you're coming, we got to
get some food in your stomach

11:37.430 --> 11:38.831
to help sober you up.

11:38.831 --> 11:40.166
I am sober.

11:40.166 --> 11:43.870
I say "Nope" to dope.

11:43.870 --> 11:45.238
Did ya, though?

11:46.706 --> 11:47.807
